<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p> If you want to create a <i>DMR cluster</i> with multiple <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short" />s in it, the cluster name for each service must have the same cluster name. <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short_intitalcap" />s in a DMR&#160;cluster are aware of each other through the DMR&#160;internal links that connect them. The DMR&#160;cluster seamlessly routes every event published to it to the consuming applications connected to any <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short" /> in the same cluster. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="SAP.SAPTempHide">For more information, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Features/DMR/DMR-Overview.htm#horizontal-scaling">Horizontal Scaling</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
        <p>Creating an <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short" /> places it in its own cluster with a generated cluster name. You can set the same cluster name for multiple <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short" />s  so that they belong to the same DMR&#160;cluster. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="SAP.SAPTempHide">For best practices  to organize your DMR&#160;cluster, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Features/DMR/DMR-Best-Practices.htm">DMR Best Practices</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
</html>